#compdef create-swarmion-app
# ============================================================================
# create-swarmion-app - Bootstrap a Swarmion serverless TypeScript app
#                       (Node, MIT)
#
# Author : Swarmion team
# Upstream: https://github.com/swarmion/swarmion
# npm    : create-swarmion-app
#
# `create-swarmion-app` scaffolds a new Swarmion project -
# a type-safe Serverless-microservices framework on top of
# AWS Lambda + AWS CDK. Swarmion's pitch: end-to-end-typed
# contracts shared between Lambda functions, JSON-schema-
# validated at the boundary, with NX + pnpm workspace
# layering for monorepo scaling. The CLI fetches a template
# from the swarmion/swarmion repo (or a custom ref), runs
# the install, and prints the next-step commands.
#
# Usage:
#   create-swarmion-app [<project-directory>] [options]
#   pnpm create swarmion-app my-app
#
# Flags (commander):
#   -t, --template <template>     - template choice
#                                   (default: "swarmion-default-template")
#   -s, --sourceRef <ref>         - example source ref (git ref of the
#                                   swarmion repo to fetch the template
#                                   from; default: latest tag)
#   -h, --help                    - print help
#   -V, --version                 - print version
#
# Positional:
#   project-directory             - destination directory for the new
#                                   project (prompted if omitted)
#
# The async-retry lane is built on `async-retry ^1.3.3`
# (declared verbatim at upstream packages/create-swarmion-
# app/package.json HEAD), the canonical Node retry combinator
# by Vercel (github.com/vercel/async-retry, 1700+ stars).
# async-retry is a thin Promise-aware wrapper around the
# older tim-kos/node-retry policy machinery: pass a fn
# returning a Promise, and async-retry will retry it on
# rejection with configurable retries + factor + min/max
# timeouts. create-swarmion-app uses it to gate template
# download from GitHub - the github.com tarball endpoint
# returns transient 502s under load, and async-retry
# transparently handles them so the user-facing experience
# never sees the upstream flakiness.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 233 :: Exponential-backoff retry policies (idempotent retry gates)
# Round 1399 :: TS-Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 233 (226th axis closed)
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : ihrwein/backoff              [R1397 _oramacore]
#   Go      : cenkalti/backoff             [R1398 _synapse]
#   TS/Node : vercel/async-retry           [R1399 THIS FILE]
#
# async-retry diverges from the other two slots in
# *abstraction level* - it is a Promise combinator, not a
# policy struct. cenkalti/backoff (Go) and ihrwein/backoff
# (Rust) both expose a typed ExponentialBackoff struct that
# the caller threads through `retry(policy, op)`; the Node
# slot inverts the API - the policy is just a few options
# bag fields (`retries`, `factor`, `minTimeout`, `maxTimeout`,
# `randomize`), and the calling convention is "wrap your
# fn in `retry((bail) => yourFn())`". The fn receives a
# `bail` callback to short-circuit on permanent errors -
# the Node equivalent of cenkalti/backoff's `Permanent(err)`
# sentinel.
#
# Across all three lanes the algorithmic model is the same -
# exponential backoff with optional jitter, max-retry-count
# bailout, callback-on-each-retry for observability - but
# the surface idiom is per-host-language. The cross-language
# interop story is at the *policy parameter* level: if you
# tune `initialInterval=500ms factor=1.5 maxInterval=60s
# maxElapsedTime=15m` in one lane you get identical retry
# behavior in any of the others. The libraries are
# interchangeable at the spec level even though the source
# code is not portable.
#
# Axis 233 closes the round 1399 cycle - 226th axis closed
# total.
# ============================================================================

_create-swarmion-app() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '(-t --template)'{-t,--template}'[template choice]:template:' \
        '(-s --sourceRef)'{-s,--sourceRef}'[example source ref]:ref:' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]' \
        '1:project directory:_files -/'
}

_create-swarmion-app "$@"
